episodes.title: 1988 Survivors Return to Jonestown | A Current Affair
episodes.description:
1988 Fox News A Current Affair: Return to Jonestown with Survivor Thomas Bogue. 

 Produced by Andrea Spiegel and reporter David Lee Miller.

episodes.title: NBC Jonestown Survivor Interview: Tim and Mike Carter and Mike Prokes, 1978
episodes.description: Interview by NBC correspondent Andrea Mitchell with Jonestown survivors Tim and Mike Carter and Mike Prokes at Guyana's Park Hotel. 11/25/1978.

episodes.title: Jonestown Survivor: Stephan Jones Press Conference, 1978
episodes.description: Press conference with the son of Jim Jones, Stephan Jones, in Guyana. Also features survivors Paula Adams, Lee Ingram, and  Touchette. 11/21/1978

episodes.title: Jonestown Survivor: Odell Rhodes speaks out on Jonestown and Christine Miller. 11/24/1978
Rare Jonestown Interview: Stephan Jones, Jim Jones' Son, Press Conference 1978
episodes.description: Jonestown Survivor Interview: News Press Conference with Stephan Jones, the surviving biological son of Jim Jones, Paula Adams, Deborah Touchette, and Lee Ingram. 11/21/1978

episodes.title: State Department Speaks out on Jonestown: Press Conference, 1978
episodes.description:
An early State Department news press conference on Leo Ryan's visit to Guyana and the Jonestown incident by spokesman Tom Reston, 11/19/1978. 

Spokesman Tom Reston is the brother of novelist James Reston Jr., who published Our Father Who Art in Hell, an 1981 investigation into Jonestown.

episodes.title: Jonestown Walkthrough Tour News Footage, 1978
episodes.description: Rare Jonestown walkthrough tour with the Guyanese and American officials. Features footage of the American Embassy in Georgetown with U.S. Consul Doug Ellice. 11/26/1978.

episodes.title: Rare Jonestown Walkthrough Aftermath Tour, 1978
episodes.description: ABC News Walkthrough of Jonestown by Correspondent Al Dale, 11/27/1978.

episodes.title: Rare Unabomber Ted Kaczynski Arrest and Cabin News Footage
episodes.description:
Compliation of Ted Kaczynski News Footage, 1996. 

Includes footage of Kaczynski being escorted into court, his cabin, and places he visited.

episodes.title: Jonestown Survivor: Journalist Charles Krause, Interview with Bernard Shaw
episodes.description:
Rare Jonestown Survivor interview with former Washington Post journalist Charles Krause by Bernard Shaw, 11/22/1978.

Krause visited Jonestown in 1978 along with Congressman Leo Ryan's delegation and survived the Port Kaituma airstrip incident ordered by Jim Jones.

episodes.title: Rare Jonestown Survivor Interview: Tim and Mike Carter 1978
episodes.description:
Interview with Peoples Temple Jonestown survivors Mike and Tim Carter by ABC reporter Bill Stewart, 12/1/1978. 

To learn about what happened to the Jonestown survivors, see: https://jonestown.sdsu.edu/?page_id=124784

episodes.title: 1978 Jonestown Interview with Joe Holsinger, Aide to Leo Ryan
episodes.description: Interview with Joe Holsinger---aide to Congressman Leo Ryan---on the Jonestown Massacre, 11/20/1978

episodes.title: Jonestown Aftermath: Survivor Interviews 1978
episodes.description: Interviews with Peoples Temple/Jonestown Survivors (Laura Johnston Kohl) after they arrive back in the United States, 12/7/1978.

episodes.title: Rare Jonestown Survivor Interview: Odell Rhodes 1978
episodes.description:
Interview with Peoples Temple Jonestown Survivor Odell Rhodes at Guyana's Park Hotel, 11/24/1978.
For an analysis of Odell Rhodes and other survivors, check out this article: https://jonestown.sdsu.edu/?page_id=128453

episodes.title: Rare NBC Jonestown 1978 Survivor Interviews - Larry Layton, Tim Carter,  Mike Prokes
episodes.description: November 22, 1978, NBC broadcast featuring brief interviews with survivors Larry Layton, Tim and Mike Carter, and Mike Prokes in Port Kaituma.

episodes.title: ABC CBS Jonestown Massacre Survivor Interviews - 1979 Anniversary
episodes.description: A compilation of 1979 ABC and CBS Jonestown Massacre interviews with survivor Tim Carter, Steven Katsaris, Fred Lewis, and others.
